  "prompt": "Which optional subjects can I choose for the IAS exam?",
  "response": "For the UPSC Civil Services Examination (IAS), candidates can choose from a wide range of optional subjects during the Mains exam. Some popular optional subjects include:\n\n1. Literature-based subjects:\n- English Literature\n- Hindi Literature\n- Sanskrit Literature\n- Tamil Literature\n- Other regional language literatures\n\n2. Social Science subjects:\n- Sociology\n- Political Science\n- Public Administration\n- History\n- Geography\n- Anthropology\n- Psychology\n\n3. Science subjects:\n- Mathematics\n- Physics\n- Chemistry\n- Botany\n- Zoology\n- Medical Science\n- Agriculture\n- Veterinary Science\n\n4. Other subjects:\n- Law\n- Commerce\n- Management\n- Economics\n- Philosophy\n- Statistics\n\nCandidates can choose one optional subject from the UPSC's list of approved subjects. The choice depends on factors like:\n- Personal interest\n- Academic background\n- Scoring potential\n- Availability of study materials\n- Coaching support\n\nIt's recommended to:\n- Select a subject you're genuinely interested in\n- Have a strong academic foundation in the chosen subject\n- Analyze previous years' question papers and trends",
